title: "Google agrees $700m Play Store settlement"
text: "Google has agreed to a $700 million settlement over allegations of stifling competition in its Play Store on Android devices. This deal follows a lawsuit by US states and a related victory by Epic Games against Google."

title: "Google to pay compensation to millions of US customers after Play Store court case"
text: "Google will pay out $700m (Â£550m) and allow more competition on its Play Store after it was accused of using illegal restrictions and overcharging consumers when they buy items in apps."

title: "Google agrees to pay $700m after antitrust settlement with consumers and US states"
text: "The company was accused of overcharging consumers but did not admit wrongdoing"
